column1: I recently finished a reinforcement learning project with a robotic arm
Awhile back I made a little pygame experiment with little race cars. I used neural networks and evolutionary algorithms to make them race to complete tracks
I grew up watching duck tales, darkwing duck, and tmnt.
Is there a way to combine neural networks such that I don't have to slowly run inference on each one?
How could I use computer vision to detect sidewalk versus road?
